      "action": "Finalize the revenue-sharing accord with the Guild Wardens of the Canal Market District, accepting formal Secular Merchants' Coalition membership and a seat on the Coalition's governing council in exchange for: (1) discontinuing the subsidized gondola freight program at the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier, (2) granting Warden inspection rights on all bulk cargo departing the pier, and (3) sharing Night Courier Depot routing data with the Coalition. The Families receive 25% of all Coalition tariff revenue collected at Tower Bridge Concourse. The accord is signed at a formal ceremony witnessed by the secular magistrate's clerk, with both parties presenting the agreement as evidence of broad market consensus ahead of the arbitration hearing.",
      "outcome": "The accord is signed and immediately effective. The subsidized freight program at the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier is discontinued, ending the Families' undercutting strategy that had destabilized the Wardens' tariff revenue. Warden inspectors are stationed at the pier within days, gaining visibility into bulk cargo movements. Night Courier Depot routing data begins flowing to the Coalition treasury. In exchange, the Families receive formal Coalition membership, a governing council seat, and 25% of Tower Bridge Concourse tariff revenue — a significant new income stream. The Wardens present the accord to the magistrate as proof that the Coalition commands broad commercial consensus, including the endorsement of the Canal Market District's most influential message-infrastructure operators. The Shrine Auditors' Council views the alliance with alarm — the Families and Wardens are now formally aligned against liturgical authority. The Families' permanent routing charter at the Night Courier Depot is reinforced by the secular legal framework of the Coalition, making any Council challenge to the charter a challenge against the entire secular commercial establishment.",
      "targetLocation": "Tower Bridge Concourse",
      "tagChangeCount": 4,
      "chronicleEntryId": "b51aef0d-6d34-4fa7-b3d6-e5b26db34872"
    }
