      "outcome": "The Wardens' polearm guards withdraw from the canal approach under cover of night, ending their contested blockade of the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier. The Signal-House Families' gondola traffic resumes unimpeded, and operators who had been fined celebrate their liberation. However, the Wardens' consolidation strengthens their defensive position at Tower Bridge Concourse — no longer stretched thin, their garrison can now hold the checkpoint firmly. The diplomatic envoy reaches the Lacquer Authority's artificers, who receive the proposal with calculated interest. The Authority recognizes that an alliance with the Wardens would give them leverage over both the Council and the Families — and access to the Wardens' informant network could prove invaluable for their long-term archive expropriation plans. Preliminary negotiations begin, with the Authority demanding a steep licensing fee and exclusive rights to authenticate all Tower Bridge transit documents. The Wardens, desperate for legitimacy, are inclined to accept.",
