      "outcome": "The Authority's artificers are escorted from the Seal Verification Chamber under armed shrine auditor escort. Their copied seal templates are confiscated — though the Authority's agents had already memorized and smuggled out detailed notes on several high-value matrices. The archive is re-consecrated with new liturgical wards that will alert shrine auditors to any unauthorized access attempts. The Council's relationship with the Lacquer Authority turns openly hostile, while the Signal-House Families express \"regret\" at the Authority's overreach but stop short of breaking their licensing treaty. The Authority, now locked out of the archive, accelerates their plans to expropriate it by force during the chaos of high-water season.",
      "targetLocation": "Seal Verification Chamber",
