      "outcome": "The licensing treaty is signed, binding the Lacquer Authority and Signal-House Families in a formal commercial and cipher-sharing alliance. The Authority gains immediate revenue stabilization and access to the Families' cryptographic infrastructure — tools that will prove invaluable for forging the consecrated seal templates needed to bypass the Council's liturgical wards. The Wardens receive a terse diplomatic refusal, deepening their isolation. At the Resin Mixing Chamber, artificers work in sealed laboratories to replicate the high-value seal matrices from their smuggled notes, producing prototype counterfeit seals that could fool shrine auditor authentication. The Authority's dual-track strategy — commercial consolidation and covert preparation for archive seizure — is now fully operational. High-water season cannot come soon enough.",
